blocks.title: How do I fit in expectations in this model?

You don't decide what resources you have

Nature does


You only decide how you use these resources


You are tasked as the user of the resources nature make available to you


You just play the hand that you're dealt
True helpfulness
blocks.body:
To do what truly helps


What is truly helpful helps the whole?

No. If you're in position to help the whole with your actions, the for sure do it.

Take care of what is important to you.


Should the stoic native leave their tribe to help the whole?


True

  • Ground truth
  • Reason

Recognizing what is true and what isn't

Avoiding all falsehood

Free from illusions

Free from distractions

Seeing things with clear eyes

Free from irrationality


What truly helps the future and those living in it

That which is right

That which is good


Even if you don't know exactly what truly helps

You can test, experiment, practice

Try things you never tried before

Try things your mind keeps telling you it won't help


Sometimes true helpfulness is to rest in preparation for the next day

Sometimes true helpfulness is to quickly grab onto the resources nature makes available to you

Sometimes it is to speak

Sometimes it is to end one's life


Difference


True helpfulness is living in complete harmony with nature

Letting nature do its thing and reacting without attachment

blocks.title: Very often in life, people grab onto things that don't help.
Stoicism helps to differentiate what helps and what doesn't
Genuine pursuit
blocks.body:
Keep trying one's best to use one's limited resources


We aren't born with perfect resources

Closed systems


Genuine

  • Always give one's best

To the limits of one's resources

Following what seems true according to one's own reasoning

Limited by one's resources

Limited by one's nature

Recognizing one's ignorance


Vice happens when you lie to yourself

When your actions aren't compatible with your available resources

That is, when you don't do your best


Pursuit

Efforts


Attempts

Results never guaranteed


Continuous

Unyielding

Incessant


Making mistakes

Learning from mistakes


Using one's ability to reason


Despite nature being uncontrollable

Almost like you keep making suggestions to Nature

Knowing that Nature has zero obligation to follow your suggestions

And reacting attentively to its developments


Attention
